{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Strengthen consumer protections on new build homes",
        "additional_details": "We believe the standards of housebuilding might only get worse with the government wanting more houses built each year. We feel these companies are not providing new homeowners of a standard of quality they assume they are paying for.",
        "background": "Consumer protections should be strengthened by requiring developers to: \r\n1) Meet stricter quality control standards before sale.\r\n2) Refund 10% of the home's value if it falls below a set standard\r\n3) Cover the cost of alternative accommodation if buyers are not happy.",
